	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />1.  I think having it end at the end of the year is a bad idea.  That is when many people will have the least amount of time.  If it ended at the end of summer (late Aug, early Sept?) then there would be more last minute time available.  That might also give enough time for carts to be sold before xmas.  8 months from now is a long time for something that isn't expected to be a complete large scale game.
<br />
<br />2.  Voting seemed slow but fine, except I didn't win!  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />  If you want to add more you could do a website poll that counts as much as 1 judge.  
<br />
<br />3.  If prizes are actually important it shouldn't be hard to find more donors.  Probably not something to worry about because I doubt there are people who won't enter because the prizes are small.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


